Movie: Puss in Boots: The Last Wish

Review: Saw this on a Monday, which happens to be the day that movies are free for senior citizens in our city, so the cinema was pretty packed. The old lady next to me brought Chinese takeout — and she nodded to sleep for a good twenty minutes in the middle of the film — and then when she woke up, she would exclaim and describe what was happening onscreen to her awake, non-blind elderly companions. And all the underwater scenes…
I BELIEVE IN DOLLY DE LEON SUPREMACY
Never knew Alan Menken songs could sound this uninspired. I was Disenchanted, all right.
I cried even more the second time around. Shocker.

Reminds me of that magnificently sketched horse with the hastily scribbled rear end.
Too many times I found myself too terrified to do anything but laugh.
